From 2f2c4aca09bdfe8cea33bb91956b30659713699f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Enrique Parodi Spalazzi <enrique.parodi@airbus.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Apr 2026 23:56:24 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 2/4] tools: add editor support for STL syntax highlighting

Add resources/syntax_highlighting/stl/ with syntax highlighting,
indentation, bracket matching, and snippets for VSCode, CLion/IntelliJ,
Vim/Neovim, Emacs, and Notepad++.

All highlighters cover the same STL surface: declaration openers, member
keywords, control/inheritance keywords, attribute vocabulary, built-in
types, reserved query keywords (SELECT/FROM/WHERE/...), literals, and
// comments. The VSCode TextMate grammar is reused by CLion as a
TextMate bundle, so the two IDEs stay in sync through a single grammar
definition.

Each subdirectory has its own README with per-editor install
instructions; a top-level README indexes them.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
